<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="830" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d830">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7370/33.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Mrs. <persName type="to">Ove
                                Gude</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-02"><hi rend="italic">July 2,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Please accept the sincerest condolences in your sad bereavement. If the
                            Department of State can render any service pray be sure to command me. I
                            offer at the same time the deep personal sympathy of my wife and
                            myself.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington
                            Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>